---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: David Naylor <david.naylor@civica.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 17 Nov 2023 at 16:20
Subject: Civica Cashless Support - Planned Changes to Telephone based
support prodedures
To: dcalvert1@archbishopholgates.org <dcalvert1@archbishopholgates.org>


Hello,



I would like to introduce myself. My name is David Naylor, I have recently
taken over as the Cashless Support Team Manager.

I have been with Civica for 17 years and have been managing the Catering
(formerly Saffron) Support Team for the last 7 years.



Based on feedback we’ve received from customers, and following a review of
procedures, we are going to be changing the inbound phone support process
to improve the efficiency and response time of support.



To that end, we will be changing the way we handle incoming calls from
Friday 1st December 2023.



All incoming phone calls will be handled as an incident logging triage
service, and not a full end to end solution or problem fixing service.

The purpose of this is to reduce the amount of time each call takes, which
allows us to answer calls quicker and reduce the waiting time before
speaking to a handler.



This means during the incoming call the call handler will only be able to
do one of the following things.

·         Log a new incident and issue a support ticket reference.

·         Update the details of an existing ticket, this can include adding
a note that the ticket is being chased, or that the priority has changed.

·         Put a caller through to the Application Support Consultant who is
already handling the incident, and who has requested the customer to phone
in.



We appreciate that whilst this means no resolution will be provided in the
initial phone call, the amount of time you spend on hold will be reduced
significantly and we are expecting to see an improvement in our fault
resolutions times.



All incoming calls will be prioritised in line with your existing Service
Objectives, and will be assigned to an analyst, who will contact you to
progress the incident through to a resolution.



In addition to logging incidents via the phone, you will have the
opportunity to log an incident directly to the Civica Service Desk via the
online self-service portal. We’ll be working over the next few weeks to
ensure that login credentials are created and distributed, and further
communication regarding this will be sent before the 1st December date.



I hope that we can move forward and make continual improvements to the
service we offer. And I would welcome any feedback you wish to share with
me.







David Naylor
Application Support Team Manager

Good question; it's a bit beyond my area of expertise and not something
I've got experience with, as the system was already installed before we got
here and is maintained by a company called SecuriPlex, who the site team
(mostly Nigel) liaises with.

However,  what I would say is firstly *if *the person who disconnected it
took photos and/or made notes, then putting it all back *should *be easy
for Vital to do. Alternatively, if they didn't make any notes, then *if *the
system isn't fussy about which cables are plugged in where (which I don't
actually know), then the worst that would happen in that case would be that
the cameras would be different to what our spreadsheet says, in which case
that would be no problem as we would simply change our spreadsheet once
it's back up and running. On the other hand it *may *be that the cables
must be plugged in a certain way and it may be a challenge to do. Vital
*might* know the answer to this, or it may be a case of try it and see!

We *could *ask SecuriPlex for their view, and if it is complex, we could
ask them for a quote to do the work, but this may not be cheap so would be
best to avoid them having to do it, unless it's unavoidable; if you do want
us to contact SecuriPlex, my suggestion would be to go through Nigel if
possible as he already has contact with them and I've not contacted them
directly myself before.

Hope this helps,

manually enabling bitlocker, this however continued to happen, so I enabled
some group policies with a script to automatically turn bitlocker on, if it
wasn't all ready, in the hopes that this would trigger bitlocker to enable
if for whatever reason it didn't.

[Microsoft Security]
We'll create a new Conditional Access policy in your tenant on or after 09 November 2023

You’re receiving this email because you’re a global administrator for Woodlesford Primary School.

In 2020, we introduced security defaults in Microsoft Entra ID, which significantly raised baseline security for organisations. Now, to build on those improvements, we’re introducing Microsoft-managed Conditional Access policies. Between 09 November 2023, and December 31, 2023, we’ll create a new Conditional Access policy in your Woodlesford Primary School tenant.

This policy, Multifactor authentication for admins accessing Microsoft Admin Portals<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Faka.ms%2FMMAdminMFA-email&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1NTUFkbWluTUZBLWVtYWls>, will be created in report-only mode<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Flearn.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fazure%2Factive-directory%2Fconditional-access%2Fconcept-conditional-access-report-only&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1jb25jZXB0LWNvbmRpdGlvbmFsLWFjY2Vzcy1yZXBvcnQtb25seQ%3D%3D>. This means that it won’t block any access, but it will generate reports on how it will affect users when it’s switched to the On state.

After the policy has been created in your tenant, you’ll have 90 days to evaluate and configure it. Then, if you haven’t already moved it to the On or Off state, it’ll be automatically moved to On. Once the policy is enabled, users covered by it will need to have multifactor authentication.

Recommended action

To avoid any potential disruption to users’ access and to ensure this policy meets your organisation’s needs, take the following actions within 90 days of its creation, before it’s moved to the On state:

  *   Review the effects and benefits<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Flearn.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fazure%2Factive-directory%2Fconditional-access%2Fconcept-conditional-access-report-only&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1jb25jZXB0LWNvbmRpdGlvbmFsLWFjY2Vzcy1yZXBvcnQtb25seV8y> of the new policy. If you don’t want us to enable it automatically, set it to Off. Or, you may set it to On at any time.
  *   Customise this policy according to your specific needs, such as excluding emergency access accounts<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Flearn.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fazure%2Factive-directory%2Fconditional-access%2Fconcept-conditional-access-users-groups%3FWT.mc_id%3DPortal-Microsoft_AAD_IAM%23exclude-users&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1jb25jZXB0LWNvbmRpdGlvbmFsLWFjY2Vzcy11c2Vycy1ncm91cHM%3D>.
  *   Verify that all users covered by this policy have enabled and registered at least one multifactor authentication method. If necessary, run a registration campaign<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Flearn.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fazure%2Factive-directory%2Fauthentication%2Fhow-to-mfa-registration-campaign&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1ob3ctdG8tbWZhLXJlZ2lzdHJhdGlvbi1jYW1wYWlnbg%3D%3D> to set up the Authenticator app.

Help and support

If you have questions or need help, create a support request<https://emails.azure.microsoft.com/redirect/?destination=https%3A%2F%2Fentra.microsoft.com%2F%23view%2FMicrosoft_AAD_ConditionalAccess%2FConditionalAccessBlade%2F%7E%2FsupportRequest&p=bT0zMjdiMmVjMi1lZTJjLTQ4M2ItYjk1ZS02ODQ5MzIzZTViM2UmdT1hZW8mbD1lbnRyYS5taWNyb3NvZnQuY29t>:

Good Afternoon Vanessa,

Thank you for raising this case regarding System Manager - Log in details.
Please see the below KB article which relates to this issue:
Error messages when editing login credentials in System Manager: "Do not
have permission"
KB0024182

Error messages when editing login credentials in System Manager: "Do not
have permission"
29-L6K8G0
Notes

When editing login details in System Manager, one of the following errors
occur when the Save button is clicked:

*"Critical Cannot drop the schema 'SIMS_[Username]', because it does not
exist or you do not have permission."*

* "SIMS_[Username] is not a valid login or you do not have permission."*

*"Unable to save: Warning: Unable to add a role membership ([value]) User
or role "[user]" does not exist in this database."*

*"Unable to save: The EXECUTE permission was denied on the object
'dp_p_user_password_reset', database 'sims', schema 'sims'."*

*"Unable to save : 41:4[DB_pit_user_user/3]:invalid value'(null)'for
parameter at password generated supplied to procedure [DB_pit_user_user/3"*
Workaround

For sites who host their SIMS database locally, to resolve this issue
please carry out all of the following steps:

*1.* In *Focus | System Manager | Manage Users* select the affected user.
Untick the 'Active' check box and save. Then, close SIMS.net. Log back into
SIMS.net and go back to *Focus | System Manager | Manage Users* and select
the affected user. Tick the 'Active' check box and amend the details. These
should now save. If this does not save and you receive the error 'The
EXECUTE permission was denied on the object 'db_pix_droplogin', database
'sims', schema 'sims' please refer to KB0023161
<https://parentpaygroup.service-now.com/csm?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0023161>
for
further guidance.

*2.* If the above does not resolve the issue, then please contact your
Local Support Unit and request Patches 19098 and 20249. These will grant
execute permissions to all SIMS objects. As these Patches are a database
install procedure and will grant execute permissions to all SIMS objects,
they *must* be applied using the SQL System Administrator credentials when
all users are logged out of SIMS.net.

Patch 19098 will need to be applied first, and Patch 20249 will need to be
applied second. Extract the zip files and apply the Patches against the
SIMS database. With all Patches, it is important to apply these at a quiet
time and once a backup has been taken of the SIMS database.

*3.* If the Patches do not resolve the issue, then you will need to
reattach the SIMS database. Log into dBattach and detach the SIMS database.
Cut the SIMS MDF and SIMS LDF out of the SQL DATA folder (e.g. C:\Program
Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL12.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\DATA) to the server
desktop.
Log back into dBattach and attach the cut SIMS MDF.

*For Hosted SIMS/SIMS Connected customers, please raise a case with your
local support unit detailing the error message received.*

How to run a patch through DBupgrade
KB0024145

How to run a patch through DBupgrade
66-B5Q2F0
Notes

How to apply a patch using DBupgrade.exe.
Workaround

1. Extract all of the patch files from the file you were sent *(onto your
Desktop, for example).*

For example, if you were sent or have "Patch 22573.zip", please extract
this to produce three more files. This includes:

3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.XML
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP.signature

*Please do not extract the contents of the second .zip file within the
initial .zip file that you were sent.*

2. Run dbUpgrade. This is located in either:

Start > All Programs > SIMS Applications > dbUpgrade
*or:*
C:\Program Files\SIMS\SIMS .net\DBupgrade.exe (*on workstation*)
C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL.1\MSSQL\Binn\DBupgrade.exe (*on
SIMS SQL server*)

3. Select '*Run the following SIMS database upgrade file*' and specify the
path to the location of where the patch file (.zip) is.

Using the earlier example, you would point this where the 3.61.870 to
3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP file is.

4. Enter the SIMS connection and login details:

- For the '*Server Name*' field, please enter the SIMS Server name and the
SQL Instance the database is hosted on, e.g. *MyServer\SIMS20XX*.
- Enter the name of your SIMS .net database into the '*Database Name*'
field.
- And then login with a SIMS username and password or you can use the SQL
SA user account.


If you are unsure of your server or database name details you can find
these via the menu route Tools | System Information within SIMS for SIMS,
or via the FMSConnect.ini located in C:\Program Files\SIMS\FMSSQL (or
C:\Program Files (x86)\SIMS\FMSSQL depending on your setup) for FMS.

Click '*Login*' once these details have been entered.

*Important Note:** If advised to run the patch as the SA user please
specify SA as the SIMS Username and enter your SA password.*

5. The patch should now show in the list, which then if you click install,
this will apply the patch against the specified database.

Depending on what is being applied, this can take some time to complete and
the dbUpgrade window may become unresponsive during this time. It would be
strongly recommended that this window is left open until it has finished.

*Important Note: It would be advised to apply patches or upgrades at a time
when no SIMS users are logged in.*

I hope this helps.

Kind Regards,

Good afternoon


We’ve been made aware that a recent update from Google has included some
restrictions for 3rd Party Apps for Education.


*What does this mean for us?*


As Google rolls this update out* it is highly likely that students will
become blocked from being able to log in to Sparx Maths or Sparx Reader
using Google SSO. This has already happened to some of our users who have
reported seeing an ‘Access Denied’ message.


*We have not been given a timescale for these updates by Google.


*How can we fix this?*


If you have Student SSO set up (or are planning to set this up soon) follow
the steps in this Google article
<https://sparx.us20.list-manage.com/track/click?u=0ac5ef746d29187afc4e50557&id=98b8e64d06&e=dcf9a9e8b9>to
set the Sparx app to be ‘*Trusted*’ and ‘*Allow for exemption from API
access blocks in context-aware access.*’


We’ve sent this email to the Head of Maths, Head of English and your
Network Manager to make sure you are all aware and are able to action this
as soon as possible and allow your students to log in using SSO.


Kind Regards

From: Rachael Maskell <rachael.maskell.mp@parliament.uk>
Date: Mon, 6 Nov 2023 at 08:56
Subject: York Peace Vigil at York Minster, 11th November, 6:30pm (Case Ref:
ZA68209)
To: <siobhan.callaghan@parliament.uk>



Good morning,

I am writing today to share details of an upcoming event in York that may
be of interest to you, your colleagues, and your students.

Right now, I know many people across York are distressed about the
horrendous situation in Israel/Gaza. We continue to hear news that
situation has worsened, and we see that there are more casualties and
deaths in this war. The humanitarian support is completely insufficient to
meet need, hostages are still missing, and the bombing of innocent
civilians has taken the death toll to more than 10,000.

We can often feel so helpless when we see these things; however, there is
something really practical you and your students can do to help, if you
would like to.

On *Saturday 11 November at 6.30pm*, I have called for a *Peace Vigil* to
be held at *York Minster*. This is an event for the whole of York, *children
and adults*, to come and see our city’s faith, political and civic
leaders *standing
together calling for peace*.

At this event, we will be creating a dove of peace on the raised altar
platform of the Minster, made from pieces of paper with your hopes,
petitions, prayers and pleas for the Middle East. Following the vigil, I
will be gathering up all of these words and then presenting them to the UN
Secretary General, the Prime Minister and the Leader of the Opposition.
There will also be an opportunity to hear some words, to light a candle and
to reflect on the current situation.

This unique event will show that our city of York, as *England’s only Human
Rights City*, is united in our call for a peace process to commence and the
fighting to stop.

As I appreciate it may be difficult for some to attend this event at such
short notice, I also wanted to provide the opportunity for our children and
young people in York to share their voices. If you would be happy to
provide opportunity for students to put down their own thoughts, hopes,
petitions, prayers, or drawings on pieces of white paper, I would be hugely
grateful. For those children who may not provide a written contribution, we
would welcome drawings too - perhaps a picture of a dove, handprints or
other symbols of peace – anything they would like to share.

My office can of course arrange collection of these prior to the event and
ensure these are added to the dove of peace, and shared with the UN
Secretary General, Prime Minister, and Leader of the Opposition.

*Do let me know if you are able to facilitate this for your students, and
if you would like my office to collect these contributions in order for
them to be taken to taken to the vigil.*

I hope you can pass on the details of this event to your staff and students
too, and I look forward to seeing those who can attend this important
event. For those who cannot, I look forward to adding their messages to the
dove of peace, as the unity we show will model what can be achieved in the
name of peace.

Yours sincerely,
Rachael

*Rachael Maskell MP*
*York Central*

From: Sue Bottomley <sue.bottomley@eastriding.gov.uk>
Sent: Thursday, November 9, 2023 8:44 AM
To: Hilderthorpe Primary <Hilderthorpe.Primary@eastriding.gov.uk>
Cc: Hilderthorpe Head <Hilderthorpe.Head.Primary@eastriding.gov.uk>; Paul Foster <P.Foster@eastriding.gov.uk>; Sean Lewis <sean.lewis@eastriding.gov.uk>
Subject: RE: Internet Issues - Hilderthorpe Primary


Good morning Toni



Just to confirm, our data comms colleagues ran tests on your circuit speed and the following image shows the speeds your school is receiving.  This suggests an internal network issue.



[cid:image012.png@01DA12E4.AF4418D0]



The above image shows the Smoothwall downloaded a 1Gb file at around 701Mb/sec, my Data comms colleagues tell me, from our point of view, up to our demarcation point, the circuit and Smoothwall are functioning correctly.



Regarding your Chromebook query, if your IT support provider can provide further details, we will of course look in to this for you, but our previous reports after the Teams meeting in October showed the fault had been resolved and pupils where showing they could log on and Smoothwall could identify them.



Running some reports for yesterday’s usage, you can see users logged in to Chromebooks and Smoothwall identifying the users.



[cid:image001.png@01DA12E6.073DA730]





We can see some pupils are already logging in to their Chromebooks this morning, which shows they are being identified correctly:



[cid:image003.png@01DA12E8.A08D0500]





We can see a some breaches come through from this week, which the following leads should have received the daily notification reports for:

[cid:image002.png@01DA12E6.6BC8A2E0]





The date variation, from the 7th to the 9th indicates below, one breach from a child using a Google email address, which was identified as a Key Stage 1-2 pupil.



[cid:image004.png@01DA12E7.0EDB7660]



The image below shows the dates from Monday 6th to today, this shows your school have had 2 breaches this week for adult content, from  key stage 1-2 pupils that has been identified with Google Authentication.

[cid:image005.png@01DA12E8.A08D0500]

This shows Smoothwall is working as expected.



I hope you find this information useful.



Kindest regards



Sue

Subject: RE: Internet Issues - Hilderthorpe Primary



Hi Toni



I am sorry you are still having issues.



We were under the impression the chrome book issues you were experiencing was resolved when Paul and Sean met with your IT support provider via their Team meeting  19th October.



[cid:image022.png@01DA12E4.AF4418D0]



Regarding the internet issues, we are not aware of any external issues with the internet supply.  When you say the whole school are seeing performance issues, is this whilst using the Wi-Fi or when the devices are plugged in to the ethernet?  Have your ICT support provider done their internal checks such as checking the Wi-Fi, switches etc?



I had asked the team to do some investigations following your earlier email, and they could see traffic growing through as expected on 25 October.



[cid:image023.png@01DA12E4.AF4418D0]





What would be useful is for you to take regular speed checks throughout the day over a week or so to see if there is a pattern of performance drops as these may correspond with either Wi-Fi demand or if there are any automated IT processes occurring, which may be impacting on the usage.  I will ask the Data comms team to carry out back office checks too.



Due to work commitments, we don’t have an engineer available to visit your site to check the Filter server, ASA until next week.



I will log a call in the meantime, if you can ask your IT providers to check the internal network in the first instance and take a log of performance drops across your site, the Data comms team will be able to check logs and carry out further investigations.





Kindest regards



Sue

Groupcall Xporter Installation Process

Xporter is a piece of software (provided by the company Groupcall), which we would like you to install, typically on the school's SIMS server, and is used to automatically synchronise the student/staff data in your MIS with the account data held in WisePay and then to update on a scheduled basis.

The recommended installation process involves:

4. Entering a Password on the "WisePay Credentials" screen, if asked to, towards the end of the install process: the correct password to enter is: groupcall2768 .

Hi Pip,

I appreciate your interest in setting up a Google Classroom within our Google Workspace. Typically, the standard procedure for creating a Google Classroom is that teachers are required to initiate the process.

Here are the steps you can follow to create your Google Classroom:

Sign in to your Google Workspace account using your credentials.
Go to Google Classroom (classroom.google.com).
Click the "+" icon in the top right corner and select "Create class."
Follow the on-screen prompts to set up your class, including providing a class name, section, subject, and other details as needed.

If you encounter any difficulties during the process, please feel free to reach out to our IT support team, and they will be more than happy to assist you.

Thanks,

Jimmy

Hi Sarah

Many thanks for this!  Well, I think I'd tried all those before half term, but I did try again tonight in the spirit of co-operation!


  *   Can you ask that they make sure when using Teams in a browser that there isn't another account signed into the browser, they could also do with checking to see which Microsoft account is signed into the device itself if it's a windows machine, this might perhaps be causing some issues.

All our devices are chromebooks or part of the Apple infrastructure (no windows here); the main way we hope(d) to log in was using Sam's iphone or chromebook for which he is the only user of Teams/Microsoft accounts. So I don't think this is the problem, and certainly trying to log out beforehand on his devices was impossible (as he couldn't log in). I also tried deleting the old accounts entirely from the devices (they remember the email address) to no avail.



  *   They could also try using incognito/in-private browsing windows in their browser and see if that fixes the issue.

Tried that with google chrome, with the same result as before.


Sorry about this: I realise it's frustrating for all parties. And curious, given that the new password you gave me at the end of the last half term worked ... once! But here we are...

Thanks

Ed

Subject: Re: Teams - Sam Venn
Good evening,
I have asked out tech team if they had any further suggestions which might help with the login challenges Sam is having.
These are the things they suggested trying:

Can you ask that they make sure when using Teams in a browser that there isn't another account signed into the browser, they could also do with checking to see which Microsoft account is signed into the device itself if it's a windows machine, this might perhaps be causing some issues.

They could also try using incognito/in-private browsing windows in their browser and see if that fixes the issue.

I know they may sound obvious but I know from using my own computers at home, sometimes once a Microsoft login is used on a machine, it sometimes gets stuck in the background and it is very difficult to entirely disconnect it!

I hope this is helpful.
Kind regards
Sarah

Hi Huntington,

Thank you for contacting Sibelius Technical Support.
Please follow the instructions below to reset your Sibelius Preferences.
Please be warned that if you have preferences set up in Sibelius, they will be deleted.

WINDOWS:

- exit Sibelius
- click Start menu (for Windows 8/10/11, press window key then type Run, select Run)
- on search bar, type %appdata%
- click "Roaming" folder or press Enter
- inside the Roaming folder, go to Avid > Sibelius
- delete the "Playback Configurations" folder, "PlogueEngine" folder, and the PlaybackConfig.xml file
- empty Recycle Bin
- restart computer

MAC:

- quit Sibelius
- open Finder then select Go > Go to folder (keyboard shortcut: Command-Shift-G) (⌘⇧G)
- type ~/Library/Application Support/Avid/Sibelius
- drag the "Playback Configurations" folder, "PlogueEngine" folder, and the PlaybackConfig.xml file to trash
- next, go to ~/Library/Application Support/Avid/Common
- delete contents in the Common folder (if there are any)
- now go to ~/Library/Preferences
- look for a file called "com.avid.sibelius.plist"
- throw it in the trash
- empty Trash
- restart computer

Please let me know how it goes.


Best Regards,
Alex
Avid Customer Care

I am just writing to reiterate what I have already conveyed to you about
the downstairs prep room being used as an office.

in there ready to go into labs etc. This room has always been a prep room.
Technicians work there on computers so they do not have to spend all day in
the chemical storeroom. The previous Head of Science only used the room
when he had no lab of his own and was moving from room to room, the
computer which became available in there and which James used was made
available due to a technician leaving. As far as I can see from your
timetable there are only 2 periods a week where there isn't a lab for you

downstairs prep room is where we prepare the acids and alkalis to use as
lab reagents and is the only fume hood available to us. Outside of the fume
hood we need areas to place what we are working on and to have access to
plugs for balances etc.

has taken up an extremely greedy amount of space and is not at all
considerate of the work which takes place in there, the screens are huge! I

Resolution:
Hi Jonathon,

I spoke to finance about the possibility of additional printers and at this stage the answer is no as all of our printers are leased and the renewal is due in 2025. To add to our current contract would be too expensive and the fact that we have coped up to this point means that a business case would not be approved. The other option is to look at how the current printers are positioned in the school and this was raised yesterday in our SLT meeting. I'm going to review our current use of printers to see if they are best placed and I will obviously take your request into consideration. I'm also looking at the second floor as they dont have a printer either and a request has been made there. I will let you know my thoughts after I have looked at the current use of printers.

Thanks

[required] Title: Adobe Express for Education - Pathfinder Multi Academy Trust
Description:
From Steve Shenton <steven.shenton@Tablet.Academy>: Good Morning,

It's Steve here from the TA Education technical support team, we are currently working alongside Adobe to support UK schools with the deployment of Adobe Express for Education. We have received sign-ups for access to Adobe Express for the following schools:-


  *   Badger Hill Primary Academy
  *   Tockwith Primary
  *   Tang Hall Primary School
  *   Hempland Primary School

I can see that they are all adding the IT Admin contact as help@vitalyork.com<mailto:help@vitalyork.com>.

As one email address has been mentioned from the above schools, the Admin Console access would be granted to help@vitalyork.com<mailto:help@vitalyork.com>, this means that all schools can be managed from one admin console. Are you happy for me to go ahead and invite help@vitalyork.com<mailto:help@vitalyork.com> to Adobe?

Once the invite has been sent and is accepted, the next stage of the process is to complete the deployment steps noted in this guide here<https://www.adobe.com/uk/education/schools/deployment.html>, you will observe videos for O365 and Google.
This step will need to be completed for each school requesting access, once the first school is setup, additional schools can be added in the Adobe admin console<https://adminconsole.adobe.com/> via the "Settings > Create Directory" options.

Please let me know if you have any questions along the way, I am here to support!

Steve Shenton
IT Support Technician | TA Education
O: 01952 567453 | M: 07411490179
https://ta.international/

[required] Title: Lord Deramore's - door fob management software
Description:
Hello Vital

Lauren (admin office) in Lord Deramore's has a problem with the door fob
management system there. It is on a PC in the bottom of the cab in the
server room and physical access to the doo-berry for scanning and
programming the key fobs has always been an issue.

Things have now got even more complicated, since someone from the CCTV firm
has been in, in that the monitor that she would usually use appears to now
be showing the cctv system. Lauren wasn't there when they did this, so
doesn't know what exactly they did!

Two questions:
1) is there a KVM switch in that cab that she should be able to use? She
said that the monitor was now seemingly connected to the cctv but wasn't
able to make sense of/prepared to fiddle with (very sensibly!) any of the
cabling for fear of accidentally disconnecting something important. If
there is, can someone please show Lauren what to do so that she can *see
the blinking software* and sort out security fobs for the September new
starters/leavers?

2) As a less immediate concern, can this software be moved to anywhere less
hideously inconvenient? I think it is running on the original PC that was
supplied when the school was built - so a machine that was second hand over
6 years ago, which probably isn't ideal - and the scrabbling in the bottom
of a comms cab in the server room is a bit of a nightmare whenever they
need to reprogram a fob. Or, if you can't help with this, can you point us
in the direction of someone who can?

We did mention briefly the door fob thing to Marcus when the easter
changeover was happening, but I think that we all forgot about following up
on it since!

Lauren is TTO but I *think* might be in some days over the holidays, and be
contacted on the main school email (lordderamores.primary@york.gov.uk), her
school email (lcharlton-mathews@lordderamores.com) or you could try ringing
the school,

Thanks
Kat
